        "id": 3218423,
        "name": "Dennis Atick",
        "username": "Dennis_Atick",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dennis_atick/{size}/429_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-18T15:49:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Nice wine. And Thanks to William Kelley for propping up the Macconais and keeping producers like Robert Denogent on my radar.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3503085&amp;iNote=9324738\"><strong>2017 Domaine Robert-Denogent Saint V\u00e9ran Les Pommards Vieilles Vignes</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, M\u00e2connais, Saint V\u00e9ran (8/18/2021)</em><br>\nReally rather wound up initially. Dumped into a decanter for a bit. Shows some honey, bready notes with a real edgy crisp apple note. Medium body, clean, a long saline finish. Consumed half bottle and last few ounce were best after being open for an hour or so. Good stuff with room to grow. Nice buy, all things considered.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
